# Trivy suppression file — list CVEs that are acknowledged false positives or
# accepted risks. Each entry MUST have:
#   - the CVE id
#   - a one-line justification
#   - an expiration date (ISO-8601) — re-evaluate before that date
#
# Format: `<CVE-id> exp:YYYY-MM-DD <justification>`
#
# Example (kept commented; remove the leading `#` to activate):
# CVE-2024-12345 exp:2026-12-31 Vulnerable code path is not reachable: the
# affected function is only invoked by the webhook subsystem which is disabled
# by default (see charts/cnpg-ha/values.yaml#webhook).
